Citation.sTitle: Isothermal vapor liquid equilibrium at 333.15K and excess molar volumes at 298.15K for the ternary system di-isopropyl ether + n-propyl alcohol + toluene and its binary subsystems
Citation.sAbstract: Isothermal vapor liquid equilibrium data at 333.15Kare reported for the ternary systemdi-isopropyl ether  (DIPE) + n-propyl alcohol + toluene and the binary subsystems DIPE + n-propyl alcohol, DIPE + toluene and  n-propyl alcohol + toluene by using headspace gas chromatography. The excess molar volumes at 298.15K  for the same binary and ternary systemswere also determined by directly measured densities. The experimental  binary and ternary vapor liquid equilibrium data were correlated with different GE models and  the excess molar volumes were correlated with the Redlich Kister equation for the binary systems and  the Cibulka equation for the ternary system, respectively.
